summary: This is a brief email regarding the completion of document unitization and coding of data from 56 DVD files in the case US v. Epstein. The sender informs the recipient that the vendor has finished the work and offers to return the DVDs and discuss reviewing the vendor's work.

events.title: Completion of document processing for US v. Epstein
events.description: A vendor finished the document unitization and coding of data from 56 DVD files related to the case US v. Epstein.

keyFacts: A vendor completed document unitization and coding of data from 56 DVD files for the US v. Epstein case.
The email correspondence occurred on November 12, 2019, regarding the return of DVDs and potential review of the vendor's work.
The document references the ongoing legal case US v. Epstein, indicating active evidence processing.
